snippet.textDisplay:
Basic pasta sauce:
Olive oil
Basil (even dried is fine)
Parmesan cheese or vegan equivalent

This is basically my lazy pasta go to. I never use a jar sauce. They repeat on me something shocking.

Another good one, but involves cooking the sauce is as follows:
Garlic (anywhere from 2 cloves to half a head)
Chili (I use 2-4 small red chilies)
Basil (about 5-10 leaves, freshly picked, or a few shakes of dry)
Tomatoes (about half a punnet of cherry tomatoes)
Dice up and cook in a frying pan in some olive oil.
Once the pasta is cooked, transfer the pasta to the frying pan with a little of the pasta water (tongs are the easiest way if you are using a long pasta, which works well with this sauce). Then add the juice of one lemon.

This is the most refreshing pasta dish I've ever had and it genuinely makes me happy. It even pulled me out of a funk and helped me enjoy cooking again.
